15/05/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- A foreign ministry delegation arrives in northern Iraq on Thursday (15 May) to meet with Kurdish and Turkmen groups about a Kurdish demand for withdrawal of Turkish troops from the region. 
Turkey has not been officially notified of the demand yet, according to foreign ministry spokesman Huseyin Dirioz. 
After those meetings, the Turkish delegation will visit Baghdad for talks with US civilian and military officials. 
(Anadolu Agency, NTV - 14/05/03)
